article_title: Four injured in head-on crash in west Oak Cliff
article_text:
Four people were injured in a head-on crash in west Oak Cliff on Sunday night.

The two-vehicle crash occurred about 6:15 p.m. in the 3800 block of West Davis Street, near West Gilpin Street, Dallas Fire-Rescue said. Crews had to extricate an unknown number of victims from the vehicles.

Three ambulances took patients to Methodist Dallas Medical Center and one went to Cook Children’s Medical Center.

Their conditions were not available.
